        <tr>
          <td colspan="2"><span
class="postbody">Atroxan, I have to say I agree with you.
<br />

<br />
     I was in the beta for WoW for about 3 months before open, the community was there at that point and time because it was selective and there was a sense of needing one another. Once OB hit, that went away as the B-net kiddies flooded in like so much the detritus they are. Then came the whines, gripes, bitchs and  moans. Everyone of them crying about the sand in their coony.
<br />

<br />
     "Well", I said to my friends and guild, "we will see what comes, most of these kiddos dont even know what a MMO is about. Things will pick up once the hardcore get going and put out what needs to happen."
<br />
     
<br />
     Which has.  Here we sit, waiting, wanting, screaming to the skies for a content patch, a fix for multiple classes, a challenge to end them all. Thats what I was expecting.
<br />
      Then most of my guild hit upper 50's and nothing was happening. Thats  alright, they just lvled pretty quickly and have probably burned. Wait, no, thats not it. They just dont care because, really, there is nothing there. Oh, MC you say? well, whatever is done could be an exploit. Scholo? buggy, crap loot, Strath, ditto.
<br />

<br />
     Then one of my steady group members and I came to an outstanding conclusion. We need to reroll as trinity classes.
<br />
      Out comes the new defense spec warrior and holy/disc priest, ready to rock the world.  And it was rocked, till we hit mid-lvl and  just    kinda   stopped   splaying...
<br />

<br />
      At this point, still no content patch. Im checking thier forums every day, wondering, hoping they are doing something cool, putting out something thats interesting. Hell, I am not the pvper, but I'll give them battlegrounds a whirl, as long as its something cool to do. Nothing. 
<br />

<br />
     So, as per usual daily routine, swing by the FoH main boards and check to see whats going down and I see a new baord has opened, one for EQ2, and the thought beings, No, not EQ again, sweet jesus no." My WoW time almost non-existant at this point. Then I start readin more info on EQ2, seeing that, even though stuff is fucked up, the devs are remotely up on it, theres something going on, in of so far, pretty frequent fixs going in. So I continue to surf about, getting more info, getting the consensus on it, what kind of Pve does it offer, is it hardcore, is it busted to hell and back, is it worth it.
<br />

<br />
      So here I am, havent logged into WoW, EQ 2 icon sitting ther, all a-quiver with anticipation at when it gets to be clicked yet again, and I can say, even at this early point in the game, its more fun, more there, more challenge, more of a kick to the taint, but Im digging it. After searching around, contrasting and comparing, it seems like, at this point in the venture, its going to be the PvE game that myself and crew were looking for, something to shoot for, but thats something really, between the two, that only time will truely tell.</span><span
class="gensmall"></span></td>
