          <td colspan="2"><span
class="postbody">I have an 11 rogue, an 8 fighter, 8 mage, and 4 priest.
<br />

<br />
Already I feel more accomplishment and power with them than I ever did in WoW.
<br />

<br />
I knew EQ had its problems, but at least content was added all the time.
<br />

<br />
I know WoW is new, but jesus christ, FIX SOMETHING.
<br />

<br />
Reading about the one guy being locked out of MC for 5 weeks for example.. what the fuck? No wonder people are quitting.
<br />

<br />
I didn't even touch on how absolutely boring PvP is. No gain and no loss, except a maximum 5 min corpse run in most cases. The only 'fun' part of it is getting the jump on someone, even then its minimal. I can't even tell you how many times both factions crossed paths and didn't bat an eye. A good deal of players don't care to bother with it because its nothing more than a waste of time, which to a point it is. You have nothing to defend, nor anything to take. Maybe all of this is coming at SOME point, but I bought the game being told it was IN the game. Isn't it even in the manual? Oh well, I don't have the time to wait until Blizzard wants to make some sort of change. PvP is what I was told made WoW so fun from the beta posts and my friends that had the beta. So... what happened?</span><span
class="gensmall"></span></td>
