          <td colspan="2"><span
class="postbody">I played wow since beta, and started retail on the destromath server.  Worked on a priest and got his ass upto 60 so that I could do the "endgame" and PvP.  
<br />

<br />
To this point endgame is a joke, their is only one zone (molten core) and its buggy as all hell.  PvP consists of ganking people while they are leveling, as the battlegrounds havn't been added as of yet.
<br />

<br />
Needless to say, I started playing EQ2 last week and Im loving it.  Its like I'm actually playing a real mmo again.  
<br />

<br />
Wow didnt have a xp penalty on death, except for a bit of durability loss.   Basically this means that any shit for brains no talent fuck could get their way to 60, and all of the content seemed to be scaled to this crowd as well.
<br />

<br />
Meh, wish I started with EQ2 when it came out instead of wow.</span><span
class="gensmall"></span></td>
